<div class="hero"><div class="container">
<h1>Can Bankruptcy Stop an Eviction?</h1>
<p class="subtitle">A free guide for Missouri/Kansas residents considering bankruptcy. Filed in W.D. Mo. / D. Kan..</p>
</div></div>
<section><div class="container">
<div class="card">
<h2>What You Need to Know</h2>
<p>The <a href="https://automaticstay.org/" title="automatic stay">automatic stay</a> under <a href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/11/362" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Section 362</a> temporarily halts most eviction proceedings. However, Section 362(b)(22) limits protection if your landlord already has a judgment for possession. In <a href="https://chapter7vs13.org/" title="Chapter 13">Chapter 13</a>, you may be able to cure rent arrears through your plan. Timing matters - file before the judgment if possible.</p>
<p>Filed in <strong>W.D. Mo. / D. Kan.</strong>. Courthouse: 400 E. 9th St, KC MO / 500 State Ave, KC KS.</p>
</div>
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<details class="faq-item"><summary>Can Bankruptcy Stop an Eviction?</summary><div class="answer"><p>The <a href="https://automaticstay.org/" title="automatic stay">automatic stay</a> under Section 362 temporarily halts most eviction proceedings. However, Section 362(b)(22) limits protection if your landlord already has a judgment for possession. In <a href="https://chapter7vs13.org/" title="Chapter 13">Chapter 13</a>, you may be able to cure rent arrears through your plan. Timing matters - file before the judgment if possible.</p></div></details>
<details class="faq-item"><summary>Does this apply in Missouri/Kansas?</summary><div class="answer"><p>Yes. This applies to W.D. Mo. / D. Kan.. Local trustee practices may vary. Consult a qualified attorney.</p></div></details>
<details class="faq-item"><summary>Where is the courthouse?</summary><div class="answer"><p>400 E. 9th St, KC MO / 500 State Ave, KC KS.</p></div></details>
</div></section>
